    "reasoning": "Given f(xy)=f(x)+f(y)+1 and f(2)=0, define g(x)=f(x)+1. Then g(xy)=g(x)+g(y), so g is a continuous logarithmic function: g(x)=c log x. Using f(2)=0 gives g(2)=1, so 1=c ln 2, hence c=1/ln 2 and g(x)=log_2 x. Then k = g(2)+1 = 2. Compute N = k^(k^2)=2^(2^2)=16. The equation N^(N^N)=k^(k^x) becomes 16^(16^16)=2^(2^x). Simplify left side: 16=2^4, so 16^(16^16)=(2^4)^(16^16)=2^{4*16^16}. Since 16^16=(2^4)^16=2^{64}, we have 4*16^16=2^2*2^{64}=2^{66}. Thus left side is 2^{2^{66}}. Right side is 2^{2^x}. Equating exponents gives 2^{66}=2^x, so x=66.",
    "answer": "66"
}
